{"word":"καταδουλόω","slug":"καταδουλόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>καταδουλόω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ώσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to reduce to slavery, enslave</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>καταδεδούλωντο, κατεδουλώθησαν</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to make a slave to oneself, to enslave</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: so in <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to enslave in mind</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}